                Parameter Tree:

                
                    EARTH SCIENCE > LAND SURFACE > LANDSCAPE > RECLAMATION/REVEGETATION/RESTORATION

                

                Definition:

                
                    RESTORATION: The processes by which an area is treated in  an attempt
to restore original conditions.  RECLAIMATION: The process of reconverting
land to other  forms of productive uses.  REVEGETATION: Reestablishment
of vegetation which may take  place naturally or be induced by humans
through seeding or transplanting. 

                

                
